5. Himera amnis. There were two rivers of this name in Sicily; one flowing from south to north past the city of Himera, the other a little more eastward flowing from north to south : the latter, which is here meant, is a much larger river than the former, and is famous as the scene os many battles.

VII. 2. Leontinos. Leontini (now Lentini) was a Greek colony os Chalcidian origin, north of Syracuse, about eight miles from the sea, founded 13.c. 730. At this time it was subject to Syracuse, the sovereignty having been secured to Hiero hy his treaty with the Romans in 13.c. 263, (ch. iv. § 5.)
